tis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remarkably, Duplantis' record of 6.25m is his ninth world record.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, his NINTH.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American Sam Kendricks gets the silver and Emmanouil Karalis secures the bronze medal for Greece.\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2457, \"end\": 2465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996890840213593, \"rank\": 0.00030710609708357205, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2466, \"end\": 2479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Kendricks\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\"}, {\"begin\": 2500, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanouil_Karalis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanouil Karalis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanouil_Karalis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanouil_Karalis\"}, {\"begin\": 2547, \"end\": 2553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.058626463468039e-16, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's an astonishing gold medal for Great Britain's Keely Hodgkinson!\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2624, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2591, \"end\": 2604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997252689732, \"rank\": 1.949734008321773e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2607, \"end\": 2623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hodgkinson, one of Team GB's great hopes at this summer's Games, produced a masterclass in 800m running to clinch gold at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"score\": 0.7362912761589807, \"rank\": 0.3581581534106004, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\"}, {\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999963329174, \"rank\": 3.6667762849722273e-09, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2752, \"end\": 2767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old dug deep to secure victory and had to hold off a strong challenge at the death from both Tsige Dguma and Mary Moraa, who claimed silver and bronze respectively.\", \"from\": 2770, \"to\": 2946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"score\": 0.7745903903867338, \"rank\": 0.28277823526652535, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not get much better than that\\u2026  It's gold for Kenya's Beatrice Chepkoech after an absorbing women's 5,000m final!\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 3069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9975912688702593, \"rank\": 0.00165146516517611, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3010, \"end\": 3028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chepkoech\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beatrice Chepkoech\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chepkoech\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chepkoech\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faith Kipyegon held the lead heading into the final bend at the Stade de France, but failed to hold off a stunning late charge from her compatriot and appeared to have finished second.\", \"from\": 3071, \"to\": 3255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3071, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Kipyegon was subsequently disqualified following a mid-race tussle with Gudaf Tsegay, which saw th